     7.)
     The output for the code is *
     
     int n = 8;
     int 1 = 10;
     while (i < n)
      {
         Console.Write("*");
         i++
      }
      The output for the code is the same (*)
      
      8.)
      You can combine true or false values by using the boolean operaters. Boolean operaters use true or false values as operands and make new true or false values.
          
        


